# JS Toolbox - English Version

## Project Overview
This is an English version of JS Toolbox, a JavaScript tools and libraries collection website. The project is built with Next.js and focuses on providing a comprehensive directory of JavaScript development tools.

## Language Requirements
- All code comments, documentation, and user-facing text should be in English
- Variable names, function names, and component names should use English
- File names and directory names should use English
- API responses and error messages should be in English

## Code Style Guidelines
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Follow React best practices with functional components and hooks
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Implement responsive design principles
- Follow Next.js 13+ App Router conventions

## Component Structure
- Components should be organized in the `src/components` directory
- Page components should be in `src/app` following Next.js App Router structure
- Use proper TypeScript interfaces for props and data structures
- Implement proper error handling and loading states

## Content Management
- All text content should be in English
- No internationalization is needed for this English-only version
- Content should be directly written in components and pages
- Maintain consistent English terminology throughout the application

## Data Management
- Use proper data fetching patterns with Next.js
- Implement caching strategies where appropriate
- Handle loading and error states gracefully
- Use TypeScript interfaces for all data structures

## UI/UX Guidelines
- Follow modern web design principles
- Ensure accessibility compliance (WCAG guidelines)
- Implement dark/light theme support
- Use consistent spacing and typography
- Provide smooth animations and transitions

## Performance Considerations
- Optimize images and assets
- Implement proper code splitting
- Use Next.js built-in optimizations
- Monitor and optimize Core Web Vitals

## Testing
- Write unit tests for utility functions
- Implement component testing where appropriate
- Ensure responsive design works across devices
- Test accessibility features

## Deployment
- The project is deployed on Vercel
- Ensure all environment variables are properly configured
- Monitor build performance and bundle size
- Implement proper SEO meta tags and structured data 